description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Safeguarding Children and Paediatric Liaison Administrator to join our friendly Safeguarding Children&#39;s team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a committed, enthusiastic and self-motivated administrator to join our well established team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for ensuring any calls from families, Trust staff and partner agencies are handled sensitively and efficiently and transferred to the most appropriate member of the team. Discharge summaries will be reviewed daily alongside our information sharing criteria and Section 17/47 requests will be undertaken. You will be expected to maintain a varying set of databases and share information with the community in a timely fashion. You will also support the team with cases where children are not brought to their appointments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post is currently subject to banding confirmation (Band 3) and is therefore subject to change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proposed Interview date - Thursday 26th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTina O&#39;SullivanJob titleLead Paediatric Liaison/Safeguarding Children&#39;s NurseEmail addresstina.osullivan@nhs.netTelephone number07880051530&lt;/p&gt;
